When we've grown accustomed to getting bad news nearly every day, it's nice to see people put their differences aside and come together to do good, even if it is only for a weekend.\r

I missed SGDQ this year, so I definitely had to give something this time around. Thank you to everyone who made this event possible on such short notice. Name: CaptainKefka
Comment: Fellow Houstonian here. Got back yesterday from a drive to Austin after having to pick up my parents from the airport there. Their flights back home had all been canceled so it was the only real option, but I'm just glad they're back safe. Despite being locked in my home for a week, I'm fortunate to say that I'm okay, but because I live on a bayou many of my neighbors were flooded badly and some family members were temp evacuated late in the evening. After settling down after this week of unbearable stress this GDQ gives me hope for the 1 million displaced in my home state. Things won't ever be the same driving downtown, but I know the people here and we'll get through it together. Thank you for this. Much love and good luck on the runs everyone.

It's gonna be a long recovery period, but with these donations, hopefully those without permanent shelters can at least have food in their stomachs. Thank you again, GDQ, from the bottom of my heart. Name: S. G. S.
Comment:
Thank y'all so much for donating to Houston Food Bank. As a resident of the outer edge of the huge area effected by the hurricane, I've been reminded everyday of the trouble my neighbors in the Houston area are in... I've been wondering what I can do to help every time I meet a stranger that was just waiting around for roads to open up so they could see how much of their home was damaged or destroyed. I am so grateful that I am able to help just a little through Harvey Relief Done Quick. Thank you!\r

P.S. Kill the animals; Save the Frames!

Name: Tumult
Comment:
This section allows you to put your donation to one of our many challenges and choices. Find the choice you wish to use (the filter box will help you find it), select it, and enter the amount of your donation you want to apply to that choice. If you wish to choose a name, you will need to use the bid suggestion box on the left, due to software limitations. You may split your donation up as many as 10 ways by clicking the "Add Another" link.\r
If you aren't sure what to put your money towards, click the 'Group' dropdown and select 'Suggestions', we may periodically add house favorites! (e.g. Runner's Choice)\r
You do not need to put your donation towards a prize. You are automatically entered into any prize you are eligible for at the time the donation is received by us.\r
